 {"id":"br-r37-c1-sgjko","title":"parity: time-respecting isomorphism matchers missing","description":"NetworkX exposes TimeRespectingGraphMatcher(G1, G2, temporal_attribute_name, delta) and TimeRespectingDiGraphMatcher(G1, G2, temporal_attribute_name, delta). FrankenNetworkX does not export these classes, leaving temporal VF2 matcher API unavailable. Add wrappers that convert FrankenNetworkX graph objects via _networkx_graph_for_parity and delegate to NetworkX, plus parity tests for signatures and isomorphism mappings on temporal graph/digraph paths.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:31:58.717555427Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:35:34.565138940Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:35:34.563236879Z","close_reason":"Completed in 739ccaa","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-vw7p2","title":"parity: connectivity is_locally_k_edge_connected missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.connectivity.is_locally_k_edge_connected(G, s, t, k) tests local k-edge-connectivity between s and t. Not exposed by franken_networkx. Add Python wrapper delegating to networkx and export at top-level.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T11:51:45.929293966Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T13:04:46.859016482Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T13:04:46.857171079Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 4eb0d6d: is_locally_k_edge_connected verified P5/K4","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-wpydo","title":"parity: community leiden_communities + leiden_partitions missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.community.leiden_communities(G, ...) and leiden_partitions(G, ...) (Leiden community detection algorithm) not exposed by franken_networkx. Add Python wrappers delegating to nx.algorithms.community via _call_networkx_community_for_parity. Export both at top-level and include in __all__ under community detection section.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T12:06:41.073069778Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T13:05:29.824008425Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T13:05:29.822140820Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 4eb0d6d: leiden_communities/partitions wrappers; mirrors nx NotImplementedError parity","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"br-r37-c1-wxjtp","title":"parity: utils.rcm + utils.misc test-helpers wrappers (7 functions)","description":"Two clusters of nx utilities not surfaced by franken_networkx. (1) RCM ordering family from networkx.utils.rcm: cuthill_mckee_ordering(G, heuristic), connected_cuthill_mckee_ordering(G, heuristic), pseudo_peripheral_node(G) — companions to the already-shipped reverse_cuthill_mckee_ordering. (2) Test/utility helpers from networkx.utils.misc: edges_equal(edges1, edges2, *, directed=False), graphs_equal(g1, g2), nodes_equal(nodes1, nodes2), make_list_of_ints(sequence) — heavily used by nx test suites. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py exporting at top-level and adding to __all__.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T21:38:45.270718699Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T21:38:45.270718699Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-wxjtp","title":"parity: utils.rcm + utils.misc test-helpers wrappers (7 functions)","description":"Two clusters of nx utilities not surfaced by franken_networkx. (1) RCM ordering family from networkx.utils.rcm: cuthill_mckee_ordering(G, heuristic), connected_cuthill_mckee_ordering(G, heuristic), pseudo_peripheral_node(G) — companions to the already-shipped reverse_cuthill_mckee_ordering. (2) Test/utility helpers from networkx.utils.misc: edges_equal(edges1, edges2, *, directed=False), graphs_equal(g1, g2), nodes_equal(nodes1, nodes2), make_list_of_ints(sequence) — heavily used by nx test suites. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py exporting at top-level and adding to __all__.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T21:38:45.270718699Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T21:43:43.115902205Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-xditv","title":"parity: fruchterman_reingold_layout numeric parity with networkx","description":"fnx.fruchterman_reingold_layout / spring_layout share signatures with nx but numeric outputs are not pinned to nx for the same seed and graph. Add a parity test (tests/python/test_layout_parity.py) that builds a small fixed graph (path_graph(6), complete_graph(5), karate_club_graph), seeds with seed=42, and compares fnx vs nx node positions within tolerance 1e-6. If divergence, route to nx via _call_networkx_for_parity when method='auto' to preserve drop-in behavior.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T06:14:51.495203398Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T06:18:38.622702670Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T06:18:38.620786474Z","close_reason":"Completed in 82fb1eb","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-ygr0e","title":"parity: node_classification harmonic_function + local_and_global_consistency wrappers (2 functions)","description":"networkx.algorithms.node_classification exposes two label-propagation classifiers that franken_networkx does not surface: harmonic_function(G, max_iter=30, label_name=label) and local_and_global_consistency(G, alpha=0.99, max_iter=30, label_name=label). Both are graph-based semi-supervised learning algorithms. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py via _call_networkx_submodule_for_parity(algorithms.node_classification, ...), export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T20:49:44.313573017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T21:06:42.170412280Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T21:06:42.168295571Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 3106ac9: harmonic_function + local_and_global_consistency wrappers; both verified on labeled chain to return identical classifications to nx.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-zud42","title":"parity: community louvain_partitions missing (exposes per-level Louvain hierarchy)","description":"networkx.algorithms.community.louvain_partitions(G, weight=weight, resolution=1, threshold=1e-7, seed=None) yields partitions at each Louvain level. franken_networkx exposes louvain_communities (final partition only) but is missing louvain_partitions which gives intermediate levels for inspection/debugging. Add Python wrapper delegating via _call_networkx_community_for_parity, export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T13:47:44.957693619Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T14:22:43.059355524Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T14:22:43.057527854Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 9b2ff10: louvain_partitions wrapper; verified karate seed=42 -> 2 levels, partition contents identical to nx","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
